704778f-c.title: Brooklyn: Hamilton Avenue - 15th Street
704778f-c.text:
Hamilton Avenue, at the N. E. corner of 15th Street, showing
John M. Eelleher's scrap metal yard. Improvements were later made
here when the ares became part of the northerly extension of the
Belt Parkway. The gas tank is at 13th Street.

704769f-b.title: Brooklyn: Hamilton Avenue - 2nd Avenue
704769f-b.text:
Bamilton Avenue, at the S.E. corner of Second Avenue.
These buildings were later torn down for the construction
of Gowanus Parkway, Brooklyn's northerly extension of the
Belt Parkway system of highways.
View 2 shows the same corner with the buildings down.

704777f-b.title: Brooklyn: Hamilton Avenue - 2nd Avenue
704777f-b.text:
Bamilton Avenue, east side, north from Second Avenue
to 15th Street, showing the area after the buildings that
stood here were demolished for the widening of the avenue.
Gowanus Parkway, Brooklyn's northerly extension of the Belt
Farkway, was later constructed here. The gas tank is on
13th Street. 7ew w w. '-S~Ae NS 9 92E.
